body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
It's very clunky to work with regions at times, due to a lack of variety in ways to work with them.

**Describe the solution you'd like**

* New methods
```csharp
// use the path's own bounds from GetBounds() as the clip region
SKRegion.SetPath(SKPath path, bool usePathClip)
{
    // why do we need a whole extra region just for SetPath to clip appropriately?
    using (SKRegion clip = new SKRegion())
    {
        if (usePathClip && path.GetBounds(out SKRect r))
        {
            clip.SetRect(r);
            this.SetPath(path, clip);
        }
        else
        {
            this.SetPath(path);
        }
    }
}

// why require a whole region for this as well? Should just be able to check against a path
SKRegion.IntersectsPath(SKPath path)
```

* New constructors
```csharp
// create from path, clipped to the bounds of the path
SKRegion(SKPath path)
{
    path.GetBounds(out SKRect clip);
    // not currently possible, due to SetPath requiring YET ANOTHER region
    // why not just permit a rectangle, or use the path's own clip bounds as above?
    SetPath(path, clip); 
}

// create directly from SKRect; ideally it should _keep_ the non-rounded bounds though :(
SKRegion(SKRect rect)
{
    SetRect(SKRectI.Round(rect));
}
```

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
The alternatives are basically re-implementing these QOL methods as extension methods in every project where I don't want to have to reuse the same 5 extra lines of code for every operation along these lines.

There just seems to be a fundamental reliance on creating excessive amounts of region objects, which really ought to be tucked away as an implementation detail if it's actually _necessary_ to have somewhere; having to create a region every time I want to see if a path intersects my current region seems really strange and expensive. Doubly so, because there's _also_ no clear way to just create a region from a pre-existing path without _first creating **yet another** region_... so I have to juggle 3 regions around just to check the intersection of a path with one of them. 

---

See below, where I am implementing some of these I have a need for them as extension methods, and I'm sure I'll keep adding to them to help tidy up my code as I get towards something I can sensibly debug.

https://github.com/vexx32/PSWordCloud/blob/Cmdlet/Cmdlet/src/WCUtils.cs#L20

If there is interest I can try to find some time to fork and PR some or all of these fun little QOL ones in. They make the code _so much_ tidier.
